First Department,

February, 1946.

(February 1, 1946.) The People of the State of New York, Respondent, v. Bernard Schatsky, Appellant.

Judgment reversed and the complaint dismissed on the ground that the guilt of the defendant was not established beyond a reasonable doubt. Present — Martin, P. J., Townley, Glennon, Cohn and Peck, JJ.; Martin, P. J., dissents and votes to affirm.
